{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T06:22:49.116Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"ReLU (Rectified Linear Unit)"},{"type":"text","text":" is the most widely used activation function in deep learning, and its variants were developed to address its limitations. These functions introduce non-linearity into neural networks, enabling them to learn complex patterns."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What is ReLU?"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Definition:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Rectified Linear Unit"},{"type":"text","text":" is defined as:"}]},{"type":"blockMath","attrs":{"latex":"\\operatorname{ReLU}(x) = \\max(0, x) = \\begin{cases} \nx & \\text{if } x > 0 \\\\\n0 & \\text{if } x \\leq 0\n\\end{cases}"}},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[en.wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rectified_linear_unit)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Visual representation:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"ReLU(x):\n  │\nx │    /\n  │   /\n  │  /\n──┼─┴─────> x\n  │0\n  │"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For positive inputs, output = input (linear). For negative inputs, output = 0."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Simple analogy:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Think of ReLU as a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"ReLU machine\""},{"type":"text","text":" that loves positive numbers — it keeps positive values unchanged and discards all negative values by setting them to zero."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text